# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

An Actor-RTC EchoService provider that registers itself and handles echo RPC calls.

## Quick start

```bash
# 1. Generate Actor framework code from the local proto definition
actr gen -l rust

# 2. Run the service (registers EchoService and waits for calls)
cargo run
```

## How it works

- `protos/local/local.proto` defines the `EchoService` interface.
- `actr gen -l rust` generates `src/generated/` with protobuf types, `EchoHandler` trait, and `EchoServiceActor`.
- `src/main.rs` implements `EchoHandler` and registers `EchoServiceActor` with the Actor-RTC runtime.
- The service stays running until interrupted (`Ctrl+C`).

## Customizing

Implement your own echo logic by modifying `EchoServiceImpl::echo` in `src/main.rs`:

```rust
async fn echo(&self, request: EchoRequest) -> ActorResult<EchoResponse> {
    // Replace with your business logic
    Ok(EchoResponse { reply: request.message })
}
```
